{
  "stem": "893.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the reason for that was that we had almost daily raids by the American [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Air Force.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And every time there was a raid, the production was interrupted.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And in order to get away from these interruptions, they moved the factory to a village next to Bratislava.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So first, I commuted.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I lived with my uncle, and I commuted to the small town.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Later on, they, they told me it would be much better if I take a room with one of the farmers and, and lived there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'll be better protected.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I wouldn't be in a Jewish environment.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so we took a room, I took a room with a friend of mine and-- with a farmer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Did these people know you were Jewish?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- I don't believe they-- they were Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a Hungarian village, but it was in Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they didn't know I'm Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They didn't know my friend is Jewish, and--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Still in Bratislava.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With relatives.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my brother was with my uncle in another village near Bratislava.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I guess people were afraid to have illegal people in their house, the Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they, they told my father, and my uncle told my brother, you know, why don't you move in with your brother?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we felt, maybe, it's even a better idea.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You never know when they'll raid the Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This way, we all had different names, even though my brother resembles me very much, you know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Many people think-- you know, they meet us the first time, they think I'm my brother or my, or vice versa.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We still felt we'll take up different identities just in case one of us is caught.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my father also had a different name.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My father's name was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
